oppler factor. This variable\nDoppler factor model explains the variability timescales and the variation in\nDCF peak lag between the radio and optical emissions in different segments.\nLags of 6-180 days are seen between emissions in various radio bands,\nindicating a core-shift effect\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 31 Oct 2019 09:33:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
