ible Kraus operators is still a necessary condition\nfor convertibility under finite-round LOCC. Moreover, we show that the results\non transformations via SEP that are not possible with LOCC (including\ninfinitely many rounds of classical communication) presented in M. Hebenstreit,\nC. Spee, and B. Kraus, Phys. Rev. A 93, 012339 (2016) are not affected.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 31 Oct 2019 15:13:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-23"}
